I didn't know if he was just trying to front with the pastor, the young pastors, and he said, every meal.

01:01:15.174 --> 01:01:18.279
He said, if I'm in Japan and we're having breakfast, I will stop everybody.

01:01:20.081 --> 01:01:21.503
Give thanks.

01:01:22.324 --> 01:01:22.905
Say grace.

01:01:24.467 --> 01:01:25.128
Pray for the meal.

01:01:26.129 --> 01:01:27.211
It refocuses us.

01:01:29.894 --> 01:01:32.037
I said, do you ever have anybody like turning down?

01:01:32.838 --> 01:01:33.359
He said, never.

01:01:35.262 --> 01:01:35.602
Never.

01:01:36.226 --> 01:01:38.208
He said, Tim, people are always watching you.

01:01:39.910 --> 01:01:44.575
And he said, for me, it's a way to share faith and at least open the door.

01:01:45.796 --> 01:01:47.137
Now I grew up in a Christian household.

01:01:49.380 --> 01:01:57.208
I knew the prayer that you memorized to give grace and say thanks before you ate.

01:01:58.489 --> 01:02:03.154
And then sometimes you would, you'd go a little bit further and say a little bit deeper.

01:02:05.058 --> 01:02:06.640
And sometimes you just wouldn't do it altogether.

01:02:09.344 --> 01:02:13.069
And this idea of saying grace has become lost.

01:02:14.391 --> 01:02:16.734
It's a ritual that may have lost its meaning.

01:02:16.754 --> 01:02:23.463
It may have lost its meaning because we don't gather around the dinner table as much.

01:02:25.245 --> 01:02:34.898
It may have lost its meaning because the one time that we do say it at Thanksgiving or Christmas time, we're struggling to come up with one thing we're thankful for and we really just want to eat.

01:02:37.986 --> 01:02:54.530
I want to encourage you, whether it's one meal a day, one meal a week or every meal, that you pause to give thanks, that you say grace and watch.

01:02:56.673 --> 01:03:05.266
Watch as God bestows the blessing and let you receive the grace that you need in your life.

01:03:06.562 --> 01:03:08.184
Let's pray as Pastor James comes up.

01:03:08.764 --> 01:03:36.370
Father, we pray that you will put your hand upon us, that you would lovingly remind us whether we're in the drive-through this week, whether we're sitting down with our families and friends this week or in a couple weeks at Thanksgiving, that you would let us pause and give thanks to say grace, whether it's for something we feel blessed with or something we feel

01:03:36.450 --> 01:03:38.252
that in the name of Jesus we need help with.

01:03:41.816 --> 01:03:58.777
And I pray that you would give courage even to the spouses and the workers in here who need to do this at a time when it's meal time, but are unsure or afraid of the reception they're going to get.

01:04:00.619 --> 01:04:03.282
That you would give them the words to say to prepare that.

01:04:04.066 --> 01:04:06.589
and you would give them the grace that they need to walk it out.

01:04:09.053 --> 01:04:14.540
And as we go from here that we would take your hospitality and your grace with us.

01:04:15.722 --> 01:04:16.683
In Christ's name we pray.

01:04:17.945 --> 01:04:18.266
Amen.

01:04:20.989 --> 01:04:21.810
Thank you Pastor Tim.

01:04:26.116 --> 01:04:33.106
I love the fact that we have this period between Halloween and Christmas to focus.

01:04:33.634 --> 01:04:34.495
and to say thank you.

01:04:35.216 --> 01:04:42.105
And there are many ways that you'll say thank you this season and many opportunities to say thank you.

01:04:42.125 --> 01:04:53.340
But as a church, one of the things that we've done for a number of years is we've said thank you by collecting and pledging towards an offering for Thanksgiving.

01:04:53.540 --> 01:04:55.042
And here's the reason why we do it.

01:04:55.903 --> 01:04:57.906
We just believe so much in

01:04:58.562 --> 01:05:09.415
beyond spots and going being four spots in beyond that we believe so much in this community and the wider community that we're all a part of that we do this Thanksgiving offering.

01:05:09.635 --> 01:05:10.556
Let me tell you how it works.

01:05:10.616 --> 01:05:18.405
So we'll bring a speaker in next year, Dave Bowser is a good friend of mine and he's a missiono pastor.

01:05:19.486 --> 01:05:22.770
He's so missiono that he was pastoring in Flint, Michigan.

01:05:23.330 --> 01:05:40.374
And when Flint, Michigan and the water stuff happened there and everyone moved out of the city, their church decided that they would go back into that boarded up city where squatters were hanging out and they would begin to rebuild community after community, neighborhood after neighborhood.

01:05:40.694 --> 01:05:51.890
They went into dilapidated houses and they redid them and then they helped people move back and made a huge difference because his philosophy was if you're going to be a church,

01:05:52.066 --> 01:05:55.715
You should be missional where we have that same passion here.

01:05:55.995 --> 01:06:04.636
And so what we do is we take a 15% of everything that comes in here goes out and 5% of that we decide to collect during this offering.

01:06:04.837 --> 01:06:05.579
So here's our goal.

01:06:05.599 --> 01:06:10.290
Here's our big audacious goal that we would collect $70,000.

01:06:10.594 --> 01:06:23.188
between next Sunday and the end of our church year, which is March 31st, that every dime of it would leave here and would go to take hope to people around the world.

01:06:23.408 --> 01:06:26.572
Now, if you're new here, understand that we don't do this every week.

01:06:27.092 --> 01:06:32.418
We don't talk about money every week from the perspective of sending it across the globe.

01:06:32.659 --> 01:06:39.186
We believe that giving is an act of worship, but this is a specific offering that we do once a year

01:06:39.330 --> 01:06:44.098
that goes around the world to take hope to people who do not have hope.

01:06:44.298 --> 01:06:45.880
Here's the great thing about this offering.

01:06:46.181 --> 01:06:51.690
It's not just for missionaries, because you know in many world areas missionaries can't travel.

01:06:52.191 --> 01:07:06.834
And so we use it in making sure that we can go through online efforts, making sure that we can go through satellites, but taking the message of hope to people all around the world.

01:07:07.010 --> 01:07:09.292
So next week there'll be an opportunity for you to pledge.

01:07:09.532 --> 01:07:10.653
And here's how the pledge works.

01:07:10.714 --> 01:07:12.916
We don't, we don't have to put your name on it.

01:07:12.956 --> 01:07:15.098
You don't have to, it's between you and God.

01:07:15.138 --> 01:07:17.060
We just want to know how we're doing on the goal.

01:07:17.380 --> 01:07:18.981
So we'll ask you to fill out a pledge card.

01:07:19.302 --> 01:07:20.002
You can put your name on it.

01:07:20.022 --> 01:07:21.103
You don't have to put your name on it.

01:07:21.344 --> 01:07:26.549
But we'll ask you to fill out a pledge card and that you will drop it in the basket somewhere so we know where we're doing.

01:07:26.769 --> 01:07:27.469
And here's the deal.

01:07:27.489 --> 01:07:34.356
I want to thank you for at least 10 years you've done this and you've been faithful in it.

01:07:35.197 --> 01:07:36.498
And the money is gone.

01:07:36.706 --> 01:07:45.356
across the seas, throughout the globe, and people have come to know Jesus and hope because of your sacrifice.

01:07:46.257 --> 01:07:53.064
We're gonna ask you to do not just kind of take your ties in offering and revert it to another offering.

01:07:53.084 --> 01:07:57.749
We're gonna ask you to talk to God and say, God, what can I do sacrificially?

01:07:58.350 --> 01:08:02.855
Above and beyond my regular giving so that others will know.

01:08:03.996 --> 01:08:05.458
Here's the deal.

01:08:05.538 --> 01:08:12.512
There are many people, many people who have come to know Jesus and maybe some even in this room because of these type of offerings.

01:08:12.592 --> 01:08:15.798
And so we're going to be talking about that next week.

01:08:15.818 --> 01:08:17.080
We encourage you to come back.

01:08:17.181 --> 01:08:20.247
I know you're going to have a blast hearing from Dave Bowser.

01:08:20.267 --> 01:08:22.511
He's one of the best speakers I've ever heard.

01:08:22.551 --> 01:08:26.098
And so I'm excited about having him here.

01:08:26.274 --> 01:08:26.775
with us.

01:08:26.875 --> 01:08:27.896
Thank you for what you're doing.

01:08:27.936 --> 01:08:31.520
And as you go out the door, there's a table for night to shine.

01:08:31.560 --> 01:08:34.504
If you're interested in that, we want you to kind of connect with that.

01:08:34.584 --> 01:08:38.128
If you're interested in the four spots, the activities, we want you to connect with that.

01:08:38.348 --> 01:08:49.141
I hope you're getting a theme here that we come together and we connect together and we belong so others might believe and become.

01:08:49.622 --> 01:08:50.243
God bless you.

01:08:50.263 --> 01:08:51.164
Thank you for being here.

01:08:51.524 --> 01:08:52.946
Have a great day.

